fields.content: The lotus blooms most beautifully from the deepest and thickest mud.
fields.author: Buddhist Proverb

fields.content: Your strength is not measured by how much you can carry, but by how you rise after being broken.
fields.author: Unknown

fields.content: Every ending is a new beginning. Trust the journey.
fields.author: Unknown

fields.content: You are stronger than you know, more capable than you imagine, and loved more than you realize.
fields.author: Unknown

fields.content: The path to healing begins with a single breath of self-compassion.
fields.author: Unknown

fields.content: Courage doesn't always roar. Sometimes courage is the quiet voice at the end of the day saying, 'I will try again tomorrow.'
fields.author: Mary Anne Radmacher

fields.content: Believe you can and you're halfway there.
fields.author: Theodore Roosevelt

fields.content: Success is not final, failure is not fatal: it is the courage to continue that counts.
fields.author: Winston Churchill

fields.content: The only way to do great work is to love what you do.
fields.author: Steve Jobs

fields.content: Your present circumstances don't determine where you go; they merely determine where you start.
fields.author: Nido Qubein

fields.content: Be gentle with yourself. You're doing the best you can.
fields.author: Unknown

fields.content: In the middle of difficulty lies opportunity.
fields.author: Albert Einstein

fields.content: The best time to plant a tree was 20 years ago. The second best time is now.
fields.author: Chinese Proverb

fields.content: You are allowed to be both a masterpiece and a work in progress simultaneously.
fields.author: Sophia Bush

fields.content: Don't watch the clock; do what it does. Keep going.
fields.author: Sam Levenson

fields.question: What are three things you're grateful for today, and why?
What challenged you today, and what did you learn from it?
How did you take care of yourself today?
What are you looking forward to tomorrow?
Describe a moment today when you felt at peace.
What progress did you make toward your goals today?
How did you show kindness to yourself or others today?
What would you tell your younger self about today?
What emotion was most present for you today? Explore it.
What is one thing you want to remember about today?
